<div id="review_86924720" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/86924720" />
    <a title="Shomeret" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1842352-shomeret"><img alt="Shomeret" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1287428998p2/1842352.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/86924720?book_show_action=true">Jan 26, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shomeret" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shomeret" href="/user/show/1842352-shomeret">Shomeret</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1842352-shomeret?shelf=my-reviews">my-reviews</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1842352-shomeret?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer86924720" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12638196587349230352">Robin Maxwell says in the Reader&apos;s Guide that the lack of information about Leonardo Da Vinci&apos;s mother gave her the opportunity to use this book in order to write about what interested her. She used this freedom to the hilt. Her protagonist was completely outrageous in her behavior and beliefs in terms of the period, but I still found the book credible. People who want a book whose events are verifiable and recorded will be disappointed, but I liked the wild originality of Signora Da Vinci. On t</span>
  <span id="freeText12638196587349230352" style="display:none">Robin Maxwell says in the Reader's Guide that the lack of information about Leonardo Da Vinci's mother gave her the opportunity to use this book in order to write about what interested her. She used this freedom to the hilt. Her protagonist was completely outrageous in her behavior and beliefs in terms of the period, but I still found the book credible. People who want a book whose events are verifiable and recorded will be disappointed, but I liked the wild originality of Signora Da Vinci. On the other hand, I admit that I am more interested in Da Vinci's public activities than in what he may have done secretly. This is why I gave the book four stars rather than five.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12638196587349230352" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


