        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1465716259" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4382904875200012424">It took me forever to finish this book. It was a huge disappointment because it has very little to do with Leonardo da Vinci. He is written as a minor character. The idea that his mother could have played the role the author conjured up here is ridiculous! Learning a bit about Lorenzo de Medici and life in Florence was the only thing interesting but there are better books for that. Such as intriguing idea for a story, but completely off the mark as executed.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


